Rxg4 $18) 45. Kc6 {Now White should be winning.} Kg7 (45... Rd3 46. c4 Rd4 47.
Kd7 Rxe4 48. Kxd6 {and the c-pawn will decide the outcome.}) 46. Rg6+ Kh7 47.
