1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Be3 e6 7. f3 b5 8. Qd2
b4 {A variation deeply prepared by Topalov for the 2005 World Championship
tournament. Since then it has become highly popular and both players have
contributed a lot to the development of its theory. It must be mentioned that
Veselin had achieved several memorable victories with this variation in the
past two years, including wins against Anand, Kramnik and ... Leko.} 9. Na4
Nbd7 10. c4 {Anand's move, never used by Leko before.} (10. Qxb4 {allows} d5 {
and Black wins back a central pawn.}) ({When faced for the first time with the
