Black keeps sufficient activity in the centre.} 28. b4 ({More cautious is} 28.
Re1 Rd5 29. Bd4 $11) 28... e5 29. Na5 Qb5 30. Bc5 Rd5 31. Bxf8 Rxf8 32. Re1 (
32. Nc6 Re8 33. a4 Qb6 34. Re1 $11) 32... Rfd8 33. Nb3 (33. Nc6 Rd1 ({After} 
33... Rd2 34. Qc1 {Black has nothing better than 34...Rd1 anyway.}) 34. Rxd1
