unpleasant surprise for Leko, who suddenly must solve concrete problems and
react very precisely.} 34. Qxd1 $2 {With little time the Hungarian GM got
confused and went for the wrong variation.} ({Correct is} 34. Rxd1 Rxd1+ 35.
Qxd1 Qxc4 36. Qc1 $1 ({Not} 36. Qe1 Nd5 $1 37. h3 f6 {and Black wins the pawn
