15. Bc4 Rb8 16. b3 Kh8 17. Nce3 g6 {The main line of the Sveshnikov Sicilian
in the past few years.} 18. Qe2 $146 {A novelty in a position that has been
played about hundred times in practice. The main continuations are 18.0-0 and
lately 18.h4.  18.Qe2 is an attempt to improve on Karjakin's idea from the
game versus Shirov a few months ago at the World Cup. In that game the
Ukrainian intended to transfer the queen to the h-file. Anand keeps the
