the position remains rather sharp.}) 25. Qe2 (25. Qe3 $4 Rxc4 26. bxc4 Rb1+ $19
) 25... Qc7 26. Ra2 (26. Ra1 Rxb3 $1) (26. Ra3 Bb7 $44) 26... Rxc4 (26... Bb7
$5 $44) 27. Qxc4 Qxc4 28. bxc4 Rb1+ 29. Ke2 Rxh1 30. Ra8 Rxh5 31. Rxc8+ Kg7 $11
) 23. Qe3 e4 {Played after long thought. Black must look for dynamic play and
Shirov sacrifices a pawn in order to free the e5-square  for the knight.} ({
